When I was thirteen I had started to become sexually active.  The biggest part of this for me is that I was finally receiving the attention from guys that I wanted.  I had always been sexually forward, there was never a time where I didn't like boys, and I have always craved that kind of love.  What I didn't understand is that it usualy wasn't love.  When I turned fourteen I had sex with a guy tht wasn't my boyfriend, but was very cute.  I had asked him to use protection before, but for some reason that night I didn't.  It was like jumping out of an airplane without a parachute.  You kind of go &quot; oh damn I don't have a parachute&quot;, but the ground really dosen't care what, and what you didn't forget.  I had an abortion, and it took years for my parents to really trust me again.<br>
Years later, looking back on the situation I still don't fully understand the reason why I didn't ask.  I do however understand the reasons that led me to that night, and even into a couple of bad relationships after.  I know a lot more about myself and I have learned from my errors.  Most importantly I have forgiven myself for making those mistakes.  I in turn have used my expirience to show other young women what's out there.  Hopefully I can help a fourteen year old girl who could be just like me.
